==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mealy bug
<hw>mealy bug</hw></mhw>
<pr>(m⟦emac⟧l"⟦ycr⟧*b⟦ucr⟧g`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,
<def>Any of several homopteran scale insects (as, <spn>Coccus
adonidum</spn>, and related species of the families
<fam>Pseudococcidae</fam> and <fam>Eriococcidae</fam>), that cover
themselves with a white powderlike or cottony wax secretion. They are
common plant-eating pests in hothouses and are also destructive of fruit
trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mealy-mouthed</ent>⟦br⟧
